iculum of what they are going to be teaching my child that year. I had one math teacher that couldn't even verbalize her teaching methods. I would love to see the public school system, as it is run today, banished. Put a new system in place that bans unions, has levels of administration personnel, holds teachers accountable for their classes outcomes and is very locally controlled. Have the property taxes that are garnered for the schools be given as vouchers and then each parent has the control to determine their child's quality of education. What we have now is an institution that is hell bent on socializing our children  to a certain political viewpoint instead of making sure they are academically prepared. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1027" language="en" documentId="4094" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Robin Hutchison" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:51PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="16" thumbsDown="0" origId="4094" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1027"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>